The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Friday, February 25, 2005 

 Bangla asylum case

 London, Feb. 24 (AP): A British court ruled today that the government unlawfully included Bangladesh on a list of countries to which refugees can safely be returned.

 The home office didn?t immediately respond to the ruling.

 Bangladesh was added to the list in 2003, making it more difficult for refugees from that country to win asylum here. Britain assumes that people coming from nations on the list would not be in danger if they went home.

 The home office added Bangladesh to its list as part of the government?s effort to reduce the number of asylum-seekers entering Britain, but a High Court judge said today that the decision was ?unlawful.? 




